<p><font style="background-color: rgb(250, 255, 255);">During the opening session of application demonstrations at the ESRI UC, the integration of enterprise computing applications with GIS was given particular attention. Linda Hecht provided an overview of how infrastructure management within city government was being tackled by integrating electric utility schematics with basemaps. Unique to this presentation was the ability to toggle between the schematic that showed the connectivity between city street traffic signals and the electrical transformers that may be affecting a lights at an intersection. In addition, she demonstrated how an SAP system was used to help integrate the applications between different functional departments, which was aided by and IBM Websphere platform.</font></p><p><font style="background-color: rgb(250, 255, 255);">David Huffman demonstrated dynamic, real-time data integration for business applications in site selection using an Information Builders application. It is worthwhile playing with this demo by going to <a href="http://www.directionsmag.com/blog/exit.php?url_id=916&amp;entry_id=416" title="http://ibigis.ibi.com/" onmouseover="window.status='http://ibigis.ibi.com/';return true;" onmouseout="window.status='';return true;">http://ibigis.ibi.com/</a>.</font></p>     ";}s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Wed, 27 Jul 2005 16:48:00 -0700";s:4:"guid";s:56:"http://www.directionsmag.com/blog/archives/416-guid.html";s:12:"atom_content";s:1324:"
